                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.938,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 68483,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 03-724, F. Hoffman-La Roche versus Empagran will be announced by Justice Breyer."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.938,
                        "stop": 224.462,
                        "byte_start": 68483,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.938,
                                "stop": 18.316,
                                "byte_start": 68483,
                                "byte_stop": 102024,
                                "text": "The plaintiffs in this case are vitamin distributors from Ecuador, Panama, Australia, and the Ukraine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.316,
                                "stop": 29.557,
                                "byte_start": 102024,
                                "byte_stop": 146954,
                                "text": "They claim that vitamin manufacturers, many of whom make vitamins in Europe, formed a worldwide conspiracy to raise the price of vitamins."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.557,
                                "stop": 50.04,
                                "byte_start": 146954,
                                "byte_stop": 228874,
                                "text": "The legal question before us is whether those foreign distributors, the plaintiffs, who bought their vitamins abroad, can bring a Sherman Act antitrust suit in the United States against the manufacturers complaining of their injury, which is a wholly foreign injury."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.04,
                                "stop": 68.982,
                                "byte_start": 228874,
                                "byte_stop": 304630,
                                "text": "The relevant statute, which is called the Foreign Trade Antitrust Improvements Act of 1982, says that the Sherman Act, the basic antitrust statute, \u201cshall not apply to conduct involving trade or commerce with foreign nations.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 68.982,
                                "stop": 75.444,
                                "byte_start": 304630,
                                "byte_stop": 330543,
                                "text": "A phrase that, in our view, fits this case and that would seem to be the end of it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.444,
                                "stop": 88.812,
                                "byte_start": 330543,
                                "byte_stop": 383937,
                                "text": "But, the Act also creates an exception and in particular, an exception for foreign-related anticompetitive conduct that creates a significant domestic harm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.812,
                                "stop": 111.712,
                                "byte_start": 383937,
                                "byte_stop": 475575,
                                "text": "The vitamin buyers say that the manufacturers\u0027 conduct falls within this exception because the conduct did create significant domestic harm in the United States, as well as creating the harm that hurt them, say, in Ecuador, and for that reason, they say they should be allowed to sue under the Sherman Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.712,
                                "stop": 116.42,
                                "byte_start": 475575,
                                "byte_stop": 494383,
                                "text": "We do not think that the distributors\u0027 argument is good enough."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.42,
                                "stop": 131.924,
                                "byte_start": 494383,
                                "byte_stop": 556450,
                                "text": "That is because we have to assume for present purposes that the foreign harm, namely higher prices in, say, Ecuador, is completely independent of the domestic harm, i.e. higher prices in the United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.924,
                                "stop": 139.731,
                                "byte_start": 556450,
                                "byte_stop": 587692,
                                "text": "And because of that independence, we think that the distributors\u0027 claim cannot fall within the exception."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 139.731,
                                "stop": 160.356,
                                "byte_start": 587692,
                                "byte_stop": 670135,
                                "text": "Otherwise, were we to accept their argument, the Sherman Act would apply to totally foreign activity that produced almost totally foreign harm unreasonably interfering with the rights of foreign nations to decide how they want to regulate commercial conduct within their boarders."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.356,
                                "stop": 169.122,
                                "byte_start": 670135,
                                "byte_stop": 705243,
                                "text": "There is no indication in the statute or in its history that Congress intended to bring about any such result."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.122,
                                "stop": 179.301,
                                "byte_start": 705243,
                                "byte_stop": 745890,
                                "text": "For these and for other reasons, we hold that the Sherman Act does not apply where the harm at issue is foreign and independent of domestic harm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.301,
                                "stop": 196.725,
                                "byte_start": 745890,
                                "byte_stop": 815585,
                                "text": "We reverse a contrary determination by the Court of Appeals and we remand the case so that the plaintiffs may raise a related but different claim, namely that the foreign harm was not independent of the domestic harm but they were interdependent that was not before us."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 196.725,
                                "stop": 202.726,
                                "byte_start": 815585,
                                "byte_stop": 839617,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment in which Justice Thomas has joined."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 202.726,
                                "stop": 224.462,
                                "byte_start": 839617,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice O\u2019Connor took no part in the consideration or decision of the case."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
